result.formatted_address: 129 Second Street L/G Nam Cheong House, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.name: Ping Pong 129 - Gintonería

reviews.text:
Nice deco. Good selection of alcohol. Octopus dish was tasty. 

Be warned, gets super loud at night so if you go there to hang and chat with friends, you will get frustrated with the atmosphere.

You could be in New York or Berlin. Really cool space with an exposed concrete warehouse feel. Walking down the long stairs from the innocent looking front door and you're confronted with a large buzzing space full of young professionals enjoying themselves. The five different tapas we has were all excellent and wouldn't be out of place in Spain. Maybe even better than the real thing, but I guess that's why it's on the pricier side. Highly recommended

High quality Spanish tapas and drinks. Pricey though. ie. 4 pieces of bread with tomato are 80HKD (it tastes incredibly good) but still is only that,.. bread with tomato.. Good if you have spare money, else better to only go later at night to enjoy the nice vibe and music with a gin and tonic.

Cool Gin Palace located in the real heart and soul of HK Island, Sai Ying Pun, and only a short walk up the hill from exit B2 of the MTR. 

The decor is very low key and it suits the building incredibly well. 
Whilst the drinks list isn't an encyclopedia, it's full of tasty Gins to try out and service was pretty good. 

Worth a try

I haven't eaten here but the drinks are always good and the bar tenders know thier stuff.

They have a good selection of gins and gin based cocktails on hand.

Also there is plenty of seating, but the pace does get busy on the weekends.

reviews.text: A big station with quite a lot of stores after entering the gate. There are toilets in the station but beware of the AB and CD exit are far away and make sure you know which way to go before you leave the station. There is a lift to the ground level near the Exit A.

Nice MTR station same as other MTR stations in Hong Kong. Nicely managed crowd system for peak hours. Very helpful staff. Quick access to exits. Easy and fast access using octopus cards. Good facility for wheel chair and strollers. Thanks to MTR staff and management for making the journey healthy and quick.
Easy interconnections to the linked stations
One of the biggest MTR interchange stations that is famous for malfunctioned male washrooms.  Passengers, stop giving ourselves hard times.  The big Corp won't care your leak.
Good MTR station
車站附近交通購物都方便 轉乘鐵路亦相當快速
